_json.gridTitle: Creeping Charlie: Pictures, Flowers, Leaves & Identification | Glechoma hederacea
_json.description: Creeping Charlie (Glechoma hederacea) - Edible parts: Young leaves can be eaten raw or cooked. The leaves have a mild bitter flavour and can be tossed into salads. They can also be cooked like spinach, added to soups, stews, or omelet. Tea is made from the fresh or dried leaves. It is often used mixed with verbena leaves or lovage. This wild edible has been added to beer in much the same way as hops in order to clear it and also to improve its flavour and keeping qualities.
